All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.faces.component.StateHolder
public class PartialTraversalViewRoot
extends javax.faces.component.UIViewRoot
implements java.io.Serializable

Request Processing Lifecycle Operation

On initial request, this instance behaves effectively like the UIViewRoot from which it extends, delegating all behavior to the superclass.

On postback, the processDecodes(javax.faces.context.FacesContext), processValidators(javax.faces.context.FacesContext), and processUpdates(javax.faces.context.FacesContext) methods have special behaviour. If AsyncResponse.isAjaxRequest() returns false, the superclass implementation of the respective method is called. Otherwise, AsyncResponse.getExecuteSubtrees() is called. This returns a list of client ids suitable for the execute portion of the request processing lifecycle. If the list is empty, call through to the superclass implementation of the respective method. Otherwise, for each client id in the list, using invokeOnComponent, call the respective process* method on the component with that clientId. After all the client ids in the list have been handled for the current phase, reflectively call broadcastEvents() on the superclass passing the current PhaseId.

On postback, the encodeAll(javax.faces.context.FacesContext) method has special behavior. If AsyncResponse.isAjaxRequest() returns false, the superclass encodeAll is called. Otherwise, AsyncResponse.getRenderSubtrees() is called. This returns a list of client ids suitable for the Lifecycle.render(javax.faces.context.FacesContext) portion of the request processing lifecycle. If the list is empty, call through to the superclass implementation of encodeAll. Otherwise, for each client id in the list, using UIComponent.invokeOnComponent(javax.faces.context.FacesContext, java.lang.String, javax.faces.component.ContextCallback), call the encodeAll method on the component with that clientId. If AsyncResponse.isRenderXML() returns true set the response content-type and headers approriately for XML, and wrap the rendered output from the components in the list as in the following example.


<partial-response>
  <components>
    <render id="form:table"/>
      <markup><![CDATA[
        Rendered content from component
      ]]></markup>
      <messages>
        <message>The messages element is optional.  If present,
                 it is a list of FacesMessage.getSummary() output
        </message>
      </messages>
    </render>
    <!-- repeat for the appropriate number of components -->
  </components>
  <state><![CDATA[state information for this view ]]></state>
</partial-response>
if the isRenderXML value is false, assume the renderers are handling the content-type, header, and component encapsulation details and write nothing to the response.

See PartialTraversalLifecycle for additional information about how this class helps PartialTraversalViewRoot get its job done.
